==============================================================================
README
==============================================================================

An image segmentation project using kmeans and otsu thresholding.
This project works on both Windows and Linux.

==============================================================================
REQUIREMENTS
==============================================================================

Cmake
OpenCV
C++ Compiler supporting c++11

==============================================================================
HOW TO BUILD
==============================================================================

LINUX:
    mkdir build/
    cd build
    cmake ..
    make (this will generate the tester to test Otsu)

WINDOWS:
    Run cmake-gui
    Source folder : ./
    Build folder : ./Build
    Configure
    Generate
    Run sln with vcvars64.bat
    Build (Whichever you want)

==============================================================================
TESTER
==============================================================================

This project includes a tester to test the Otsu algorithm and Kmeans.

==============================================================================
OTSU THRESHOLDING
==============================================================================

Implement Otsu multi-level thresholding.
The implementation generates an appropriate algorithm for the number of class
in the input, compiles it, creates a library and calls the function generated
in the library.(I'm aware of the fact that this is not the best way to do it,
just wanted to try out and learn some new things on Linux and Windows)

